The paper discusses the DCell network structure, which is commonly used in data centers. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the Hamiltonian properties of the DCell network, which is related to the design and architecture of the network, making it likely to belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. The paper also proposes an algorithm for finding a Hamiltonian path, which falls under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories.
